dataset_description: Diabetes is a 100,000 entries dataset representing 10 years (1999-2008) of clinical care at 130 US hospitals and integrated delivery networks

attributes.name: encounter_id
attributes.description: unique identifier of an encounter

attributes.name: patient_nbr
attributes.description: unique identifier of a patient

attributes.name: race
attributes.description: values: Caucasian, Asian, African American, Hispanic, and other

attributes.name: gender
attributes.description: values: male, female, and unknown/invalid

attributes.name: age
attributes.description: grouped in 10-year intervals: [0, 10), [10, 20), ..., [90, 100)

attributes.name: weight
attributes.description: weight in pounds

attributes.name: admission_type_id
attributes.description: integer identifier corresponding to 9 distinct values, for example, emergency, urgent, elective, newborn, and not available

attributes.name: discharge_disposition_id
attributes.description: integer identifier corresponding to 29 distinct values, for example, discharged to home, expired, and not available

attributes.name: admission_source_id
attributes.description: integer identifier corresponding to 21 distinct values, for example, physician referral, emergency room, and transfer from a hospital

attributes.name: time_in_hospital
attributes.description: integer number of days between admission and discharge

attributes.name: payer_code
attributes.description: integer identifier corresponding to 23 distinct values

attributes.name: medical_specialty
attributes.description: integer identifier of a specialty of the admitting physician, corresponding to 84 distinct values

attributes.name: num_lab_procedures
attributes.description: number of lab tests performed during the encounter

attributes.name: num_procedures
attributes.description: number of procedures (other than lab tests) performed during the encounter

attributes.name: num_medications
attributes.description: number of distinct generic names administered during the encounter

attributes.name: number_outpatient
attributes.description: number of outpatient visits of the patient in the year preceding the encounter

attributes.name: number_emergency
attributes.description: number of emergency visits of the patient in the year preceding the encounter

attributes.name: number_inpatient
attributes.description: number of inpatient visits of the patient in the year preceding the encounter

attributes.name: diag_1
attributes.description: the primary diagnosis (coded as first three digits of ICD9); 848 distinct values

attributes.name: diag_2
attributes.description: secondary diagnosis (coded as first three digits of ICD9); 923 distinct values

attributes.name: diag_3
attributes.description: additional secondary diagnosis (coded as first three digits of ICD9); 954 distinct values

attributes.name: number_diagnoses
attributes.description: number of diagnoses entered to the system

attributes.name: max_glu_serum
attributes.description: glucose serum test result. Indicates the range of the result or if the test was not taken. Values: >200, >300, normal, and none if not measured

attributes.name: A1Cresult
attributes.description: A1c test result. Indicates the range of the result or if the test was not taken. Values: >8 if the result was greater than 8%, >7 if the result was greater than 7% but less than 8%, normal if the result was less than 7%, and none if not measured
